" ============================================================================
" ~/.ideameowrc — default config for the ideameow plugin
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" Copy this file to your home directory (Linux/macOS: ~/.ideameowrc,
" Windows: C:\Users\<you>\.ideameowrc) or open it in the IDE with SPC c v.
" Reload after editing with SPC c V (or the "Reload .ideameowrc" action).
"
" Syntax (see the README for the full guide):
"   nmap <key> <action>(ActionId)     NORMAL-mode key -> IDE action
"   nmap <key> <meow keys>            NORMAL-mode key -> replayed meow keys
"   nnoremap ...                      like nmap, but the RHS skips user maps
"   map <leader><seq> <target>        keypad (SPC) entry, layered over builtins
"   desc <leader><seq> <text>         which-key label for an entry or a group
"   set timeoutlen=300                which-key popup delay in ms
"   set nowhich-key                   turn the which-key popup off
"
" Ported from intellij-community-settings/ideavim/.ideavimrc. Not portable
" (and why) is listed at the bottom. The meow layout itself (w e b x s d c...)
" needs NO porting — the plugin implements it natively.
" ============================================================================

set which-key
set timeoutlen=300

" --- avy jumps, mirroring init.el (needs the AceJump plugin) ----------------
" init.el: S = avy-goto-char-timer, Q = avy-goto-line. X still goes-to-line,
" so overriding Q costs nothing.
nmap S <action>(AceAction)
nmap Q <action>(AceLineAction)

" --- split resizing (ideavimrc: - = _ +) ------------------------------------
" '-' stays meow's negative-argument (the reason ideavimrc used '-' here was
" that vim lacks negative counts — this plugin doesn't). The other three keys
" are free in the meow layout:
nmap = <action>(StretchSplitToTop)
nmap _ <action>(StretchSplitToLeft)
nmap + <action>(StretchSplitToRight)

" --- which-key labels for the builtin keypad groups -------------------------
desc <leader>b buffers (RecentFiles)
desc <leader>x C-x · file / buffer / window
desc <leader>xp C-x p · project
desc <leader>c C-c · commands (= M-m)
desc <leader>cj C-c j · avy jump
desc <leader>m M- · meta
desc <leader>ms M-s · search
desc <leader>w window map (Emacs C-c w)

" ============================================================================
" IntelliJ feature groups, ported 1:1 from the .ideavimrc leader
" (b / c / m / w / x and digits stay builtin — identical entries are omitted)
" ============================================================================

" --- SPC . — settings / UI ---------------------------------------------------
desc <leader>. settings / UI
map <leader>.c <action>(ToggleCompactMode)
map <leader>.C <action>(CloseProject)
map <leader>.d <action>(ToggleDistractionFreeMode)
map <leader>.f <action>(ToggleFullScreen)
map <leader>.k <action>(ChangeKeymap)
map <leader>.l <action>(EditorToggleShowLineNumbers)
map <leader>.m <action>(ExternalSystem.ProjectRefreshAction)
map <leader>.p <action>(WelcomeScreen.Plugins)
map <leader>.r <action>(RunConfiguration)
map <leader>.R <action>(RestartIde)
map <leader>.s <action>(SettingsEntryPoint)
map <leader>.t <action>(ChangeLaf)
map <leader>.T <action>(ViewToolButtons)
map <leader>.z <action>(ToggleZenMode)

